<div id="review_37218535" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/37218535" />
    <a title="Megan" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1301544-megan"><img alt="Megan" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1552021376p2/1301544.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/37218535?book_show_action=true">Nov 08, 2008</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Megan" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Megan" href="/user/show/1301544-megan">Megan</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780440910817" href="/book/show/14358.A_Ring_of_Endless_Light">review of another edition</a>

          <div><span class="uitext greyText">Recommends it for: </span>
           <span class="uitext reviewText">anyone age 13 and up</span></div>

        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1301544-megan?shelf=ya">ya</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer37218535" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1140962956547782118">I first read this book as an early teen--I can see now, reading it as an adult, that having read this book (along with all Madeleine L&apos;Engle&apos;s other books) at twelve and thirteen clearly had a profound impact on my world view. L&apos;Engle&apos;s writing has a depth and profundity that draws on emotions of which most writers only attempt to scratch the surface.<br/><br/>I think all developing adolescents should read this book and all its accompanying ones, if only to see that there is more out there than either com</span>
  <span id="freeText1140962956547782118" style="display:none">I first read this book as an early teen--I can see now, reading it as an adult, that having read this book (along with all Madeleine L'Engle's other books) at twelve and thirteen clearly had a profound impact on my world view. L'Engle's writing has a depth and profundity that draws on emotions of which most writers only attempt to scratch the surface.<br /><br />I think all developing adolescents should read this book and all its accompanying ones, if only to see that there is more out there than either complete surrender to the inanity of life, or conversely, that fantasy does not necessarily mean being out of touch with reality.<br /><br />I am happy that I left this book on a shelf long enough that coming back to it all these years later meant it was fresh and new while being comfortingly familiar.</span>
  <a data-text-id="1140962956547782118" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


